{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":917,"text":"Well when I was asked to do this TEDTalk, I was really chuckled,"},{"time":3280,"text":"because, you see, my father's name was Ted,"},{"time":7073,"text":"and much of my life, especially my musical life,"},{"time":11087,"text":"is really a talk that I'm still having with him,"},{"time":14208,"text":"or the part of me that he continues to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17956,"text":"Now Ted was a New Yorker, an all-around theater guy,"},{"time":21560,"text":"and he was a self-taught illustrator and musician."},{"time":25875,"text":"He didn't read a note,"},{"time":27410,"text":"and he was profoundly hearing impaired."},{"time":30375,"text":"Yet, he was my greatest teacher."},{"time":33633,"text":"Because even through the squeaks of his hearing aids,"},{"time":37070,"text":"his understanding of music was profound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40250,"text":"And for him, it wasn't so much the way the music goes"},{"time":43631,"text":"as about what it witnesses and where it can take you."},{"time":47827,"text":"And he did a painting of this experience,"},{"time":50444,"text":"which he called \"In the Realm of Music.\""},{"time":53533,"text":"Now Ted entered this realm every day by improvising"},{"time":60021,"text":"in a sort of Tin Pan Alley style like this."},{"time":62802,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69644,"text":"But he was tough when it came to music."},{"time":72998,"text":"He said, \"There are only two things that matter in music:"},{"time":75704,"text":"what and how."},{"time":77917,"text":"And the thing about classical music,"},{"time":81704,"text":"that what and how, it's inexhaustible.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":85032,"text":"That was his passion for the music."},{"time":87200,"text":"Both my parents really loved it."},{"time":89057,"text":"They didn't know all that much about it,"},{"time":91315,"text":"but they gave me the opportunity to discover it"},{"time":95042,"text":"together with them."},{"time":96958,"text":"And I think inspired by that memory,"},{"time":100170,"text":"it's been my desire to try and bring it"},{"time":102173,"text":"to as many other people as I can,"},{"time":103218,"text":"sort of pass it on through whatever means."},{"time":106792,"text":"And how people get this music, how it comes into their lives,"},{"time":111802,"text":"really fascinates me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113258,"text":"One day in New York, I was on the street"},{"time":115515,"text":"and I saw some kids playing baseball between stoops and cars and fire hydrants."},{"time":120920,"text":"And a tough, slouchy kid got up to bat,"},{"time":123621,"text":"and he took a swing and really connected."},{"time":126325,"text":"And he watched the ball fly for a second,"},{"time":128027,"text":"and then he went, \"Dah dadaratatatah."},{"time":131431,"text":"Brah dada dadadadah.\""},{"time":134917,"text":"And he ran around the bases."},{"time":136750,"text":"And I thought, go figure."},{"time":139485,"text":"How did this piece of 18th century Austrian aristocratic entertainment"},{"time":144566,"text":"turn into the victory crow of this New York kid?"},{"time":149238,"text":"How was that passed on? How did he get to hear Mozart?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":153640,"text":"Well when it comes to classical music,"},{"time":155561,"text":"there's an awful lot to pass on,"},{"time":157817,"text":"much more than Mozart, Beethoven or Tchiakovsky."},{"time":161554,"text":"Because classical music"},{"time":163166,"text":"is an unbroken living tradition"},{"time":166583,"text":"that goes back over 1,000 years."},{"time":169833,"text":"And every one of those years"},{"time":171877,"text":"has had something unique and powerful to say to us"},{"time":175375,"text":"about what it's like to be alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178600,"text":"Now the raw material of it, of course,"},{"time":181159,"text":"is just the music of everyday life."},{"time":182875,"text":"It's all the anthems and dance crazes"},{"time":185908,"text":"and ballads and marches."},{"time":187643,"text":"But what classical music does"},{"time":190333,"text":"is to distill all of these musics down,"},{"time":195193,"text":"to condense them to their absolute essence,"},{"time":198879,"text":"and from that essence create a new language,"},{"time":202167,"text":"a language that speaks very lovingly and unflinchingly"},{"time":207652,"text":"about who we really are."},{"time":209752,"text":"It's a language that's still evolving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212596,"text":"Now over the centuries it grew into the big pieces we always think of,"},{"time":216167,"text":"like concertos and symphonies,"},{"time":219167,"text":"but even the most ambitious masterpiece"},{"time":222498,"text":"can have as its central mission"},{"time":224917,"text":"to bring you back to a fragile and personal moment --"},{"time":229417,"text":"like this one from the Beethoven Violin Concerto."},{"time":232625,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":255011,"text":"It's so simple, so evocative."},{"time":260995,"text":"So many emotions seem to be inside of it."},{"time":263855,"text":"Yet, of course, like all music,"},{"time":265583,"text":"it's essentially not about anything."},{"time":268042,"text":"It's just a design of pitches and silence and time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271825,"text":"And the pitches, the notes, as you know, are just vibrations."},{"time":275917,"text":"They're locations in the spectrum of sound."},{"time":278870,"text":"And whether we call them 440 per second, A,"},{"time":282971,"text":"or 3,729, B flat -- trust me, that's right --"},{"time":289689,"text":"they're just phenomena."},{"time":293785,"text":"But the way we react to different combinations of these phenomena"},{"time":297542,"text":"is complex and emotional and not totally understood."},{"time":301336,"text":"And the way we react to them has changed radically over the centuries,"},{"time":305167,"text":"as have our preferences for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307542,"text":"So for example, in the 11th century,"},{"time":310833,"text":"people liked pieces that ended like this."},{"time":314673,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":326406,"text":"And in the 17th century, it was more like this."},{"time":331562,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":337000,"text":"And in the 21st century ..."},{"time":340842,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348250,"text":"Now your 21st century ears are quite happy with this last chord,"},{"time":353569,"text":"even though a while back it would have puzzled or annoyed you"},{"time":357042,"text":"or sent some of you running from the room."},{"time":358542,"text":"And the reason you like it"},{"time":359958,"text":"is because you've inherited, whether you knew it or not,"},{"time":362446,"text":"centuries-worth of changes"},{"time":365000,"text":"in musical theory, practice and fashion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368500,"text":"And in classical music we can follow these changes very, very accurately"},{"time":373590,"text":"because of the music's powerful silent partner,"},{"time":377573,"text":"the way it's been passed on: notation."},{"time":381202,"text":"Now the impulse to notate,"},{"time":383167,"text":"or, more exactly I should say, encode music"},{"time":385958,"text":"has been with us for a very long time."},{"time":389016,"text":"In 200 B.C., a man named Sekulos"},{"time":392917,"text":"wrote this song for his departed wife"},{"time":395867,"text":"and inscribed it on her gravestone"},{"time":397458,"text":"in the notational system of the Greeks."},{"time":400083,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427458,"text":"And a thousand years later,"},{"time":429875,"text":"this impulse to notate took an entirely different form."},{"time":433885,"text":"And you can see how this happened"},{"time":435250,"text":"in these excerpts from the Christmas mass \"Puer Natus est nobis,\""},{"time":441833,"text":"\"For Us is Born.\""},{"time":444208,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":448841,"text":"In the 10th century, little squiggles were used"},{"time":451083,"text":"just to indicate the general shape of the tune."},{"time":454125,"text":"And in the 12th century, a line was drawn, like a musical horizon line,"},{"time":461167,"text":"to better pinpoint the pitch's location."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464745,"text":"And then in the 13th century, more lines and new shapes of notes"},{"time":473090,"text":"locked in the concept of the tune exactly,"},{"time":476708,"text":"and that led to the kind of notation we have today."},{"time":479375,"text":"Well notation not only passed the music on,"},{"time":483046,"text":"notating and encoding the music changed its priorities entirely,"},{"time":487727,"text":"because it enabled the musicians"},{"time":489683,"text":"to imagine music on a much vaster scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493339,"text":"Now inspired moves of improvisation"},{"time":496667,"text":"could be recorded, saved, considered, prioritized,"},{"time":500667,"text":"made into intricate designs."},{"time":503208,"text":"And from this moment, classical music became"},{"time":506448,"text":"what it most essentially is,"},{"time":509042,"text":"a dialogue between the two powerful sides of our nature:"},{"time":514083,"text":"instinct and intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516458,"text":"And there began to be a real difference at this point"},{"time":519833,"text":"between the art of improvisation"},{"time":522750,"text":"and the art of composition."},{"time":524158,"text":"Now an improviser senses and plays the next cool move,"},{"time":528675,"text":"but a composer is considering all possible moves,"},{"time":532292,"text":"testing them out, prioritizing them out,"},{"time":535611,"text":"until he sees how they can form a powerful and coherent design"},{"time":540083,"text":"of ultimate and enduring coolness."},{"time":544490,"text":"Now some of the greatest composers, like Bach,"},{"time":546042,"text":"were combinations of these two things."},{"time":548271,"text":"Bach was like a great improviser with a mind of a chess master."},{"time":552556,"text":"Mozart was the same way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554500,"text":"But every musician strikes a different balance"},{"time":557746,"text":"between faith and reason, instinct and intelligence."},{"time":561542,"text":"And every musical era had different priorities of these things,"},{"time":566450,"text":"different things to pass on, different 'whats' and 'hows'."},{"time":570417,"text":"So in the first eight centuries or so of this tradition"},{"time":574985,"text":"the big 'what' was to praise God."},{"time":577833,"text":"And by the 1400s, music was being written"},{"time":580458,"text":"that tried to mirror God's mind"},{"time":584542,"text":"as could be seen in the design of the night sky."},{"time":588458,"text":"The 'how' was a style called polyphony,"},{"time":591750,"text":"music of many independently moving voices"},{"time":595500,"text":"that suggested the way the planets seemed to move"},{"time":598208,"text":"in Ptolemy's geocentric universe."},{"time":600837,"text":"This was truly the music of the spheres."},{"time":604623,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633917,"text":"This is the kind of music that Leonardo DaVinci would have known."},{"time":639167,"text":"And perhaps its tremendous intellectual perfection and serenity"},{"time":642765,"text":"meant that something new had to happen --"},{"time":645625,"text":"a radical new move, which in 1600 is what did happen."},{"time":649750,"text":"(Music) Singer: Ah, bitter blow!"},{"time":656583,"text":"Ah, wicked, cruel fate!"},{"time":661375,"text":"Ah, baleful stars!"},{"time":668292,"text":"Ah, avaricious heaven!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675250,"text":"MTT: This, of course, was the birth of opera,"},{"time":678958,"text":"and its development put music on a radical new course."},{"time":681570,"text":"The what now was not to mirror the mind of God,"},{"time":685925,"text":"but to follow the emotion turbulence of man."},{"time":688875,"text":"And the how was harmony,"},{"time":692167,"text":"stacking up the pitches to form chords."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695458,"text":"And the chords, it turned out,"},{"time":697208,"text":"were capable of representing incredible varieties of emotions."},{"time":701292,"text":"And the basic chords were the ones we still have with us,"},{"time":706091,"text":"the triads,"},{"time":707352,"text":"either the major one,"},{"time":710611,"text":"which we think is happy,"},{"time":715219,"text":"or the minor one,"},{"time":718564,"text":"which we perceive as sad."},{"time":722500,"text":"But what's the actual difference between these two chords?"},{"time":725769,"text":"It's just these two notes in the middle."},{"time":728006,"text":"It's either E natural,"},{"time":730971,"text":"and 659 vibrations per second,"},{"time":735687,"text":"or E flat, at 622."},{"time":740375,"text":"So the big difference between human happiness and sadness?"},{"time":746000,"text":"37 freakin' vibrations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748750,"text":"So you can see in a system like this"},{"time":752667,"text":"there was enormous subtle potential"},{"time":754696,"text":"of representing human emotions."},{"time":756571,"text":"And in fact, as man began to understand more"},{"time":760304,"text":"his complex and ambivalent nature,"},{"time":762467,"text":"harmony grew more complex to reflect it."},{"time":765125,"text":"Turns out it was capable of expressing emotions"},{"time":769184,"text":"beyond the ability of words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770917,"text":"Now with all this possibility,"},{"time":774250,"text":"classical music really took off."},{"time":778333,"text":"It's the time in which the big forms began to arise."},{"time":781729,"text":"And the effects of technology began to be felt also,"},{"time":786333,"text":"because printing put music, the scores, the codebooks of music,"},{"time":790769,"text":"into the hands of performers everywhere."},{"time":792779,"text":"And new and improved instruments"},{"time":795000,"text":"made the age of the virtuoso possible."},{"time":798292,"text":"This is when those big forms arose --"},{"time":801542,"text":"the symphonies, the sonatas, the concertos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804661,"text":"And in these big architectures of time,"},{"time":808667,"text":"composers like Beethoven could share the insights of a lifetime."},{"time":814375,"text":"A piece like Beethoven's Fifth"},{"time":816835,"text":"basically witnessing how it was possible"},{"time":821193,"text":"for him to go from sorrow and anger,"},{"time":826710,"text":"over the course of a half an hour,"},{"time":830417,"text":"step by exacting step of his route,"},{"time":834208,"text":"to the moment when he could make it across to joy."},{"time":838548,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":861042,"text":"And it turned out the symphony could be used for more complex issues,"},{"time":866083,"text":"like gripping ones of culture,"},{"time":868710,"text":"such as nationalism or quest for freedom"},{"time":871458,"text":"or the frontiers of sensuality."},{"time":875329,"text":"But whatever direction the music took,"},{"time":879100,"text":"one thing until recently was always the same,"},{"time":881638,"text":"and that was when the musicians stopped playing,"},{"time":884667,"text":"the music stopped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887042,"text":"Now this moment so fascinates me."},{"time":890405,"text":"I find it such a profound one."},{"time":892316,"text":"What happens when the music stops?"},{"time":893683,"text":"Where does it go? What's left?"},{"time":897125,"text":"What sticks with people in the audience at the end of a performance?"},{"time":900413,"text":"Is it a melody or a rhythm"},{"time":902185,"text":"or a mood or an attitude?"},{"time":904965,"text":"And how might that change their lives?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":907234,"text":"To me this is the intimate, personal side of music."},{"time":911167,"text":"It's the passing on part. It's the 'why' part of it."},{"time":915708,"text":"And to me that's the most essential of all."},{"time":918966,"text":"Mostly it's been a person-to-person thing,"},{"time":922925,"text":"a teacher-student, performer-audience thing,"},{"time":925532,"text":"and then around 1880 came this new technology"},{"time":928309,"text":"that first mechanically then through analogs then digitally"},{"time":931000,"text":"created a new and miraculous way of passing things on,"},{"time":935287,"text":"albeit an impersonal one."},{"time":937075,"text":"People could now hear music all the time,"},{"time":940792,"text":"even though it wasn't necessary"},{"time":941667,"text":"for them to play an instrument, read music or even go to concerts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946208,"text":"And technology democratized music by making everything available."},{"time":951512,"text":"It spearheaded a cultural revolution"},{"time":953273,"text":"in which artists like Caruso and Bessie Smith were on the same footing."},{"time":958133,"text":"And technology pushed composers to tremendous extremes,"},{"time":962054,"text":"using computers and synthesizers"},{"time":963754,"text":"to create works of intellectually impenetrable complexity"},{"time":966673,"text":"beyond the means of performers and audiences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971208,"text":"At the same time technology,"},{"time":973708,"text":"by taking over the role that notation had always played,"},{"time":977000,"text":"shifted the balance within music between instinct and intelligence"},{"time":981542,"text":"way over to the instinctive side."},{"time":984833,"text":"The culture in which we live now"},{"time":986723,"text":"is awash with music of improvisation"},{"time":989792,"text":"that's been sliced, diced, layered"},{"time":991417,"text":"and, God knows, distributed and sold."},{"time":995167,"text":"What's the long-term effect of this on us or on music?"},{"time":998454,"text":"Nobody knows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":999461,"text":"The question remains: What happens when the music stops?"},{"time":1003183,"text":"What sticks with people?"},{"time":1005165,"text":"Now that we have unlimited access to music, what does stick with us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009117,"text":"Well let me show you a story of what I mean"},{"time":1011537,"text":"by \"really sticking with us.\""},{"time":1013329,"text":"I was visiting a cousin of mine in an old age home,"},{"time":1016417,"text":"and I spied a very shaky old man"},{"time":1019752,"text":"making his way across the room on a walker."},{"time":1022029,"text":"He came over to a piano that was there,"},{"time":1024545,"text":"and he balanced himself and began playing something like this."},{"time":1028875,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033410,"text":"And he said something like, \"Me ... boy ... symphony ... Beethoven.\""},{"time":1042273,"text":"And I suddenly got it,"},{"time":1043825,"text":"and I said, \"Friend, by any chance are you trying to play this?\""},{"time":1046745,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":1051696,"text":"And he said, \"Yes, yes. I was a little boy."},{"time":1054125,"text":"The symphony: Isaac Stern, the concerto, I heard it.\""},{"time":1058721,"text":"And I thought, my God,"},{"time":1060404,"text":"how much must this music mean to this man"},{"time":1063250,"text":"that he would get himself out of his bed, across the room"},{"time":1067367,"text":"to recover the memory of this music"},{"time":1070667,"text":"that, after everything else in his life is sloughing away,"},{"time":1073575,"text":"still means so much to him?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075833,"text":"Well, that's why I take every performance so seriously,"},{"time":1079756,"text":"why it matters to me so much."},{"time":1081506,"text":"I never know who might be there, who might be absorbing it"},{"time":1084958,"text":"and what will happen to it in their life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086708,"text":"But now I'm excited that there's more chance than ever before possible"},{"time":1091795,"text":"of sharing this music."},{"time":1093125,"text":"That's what drives my interest in projects"},{"time":1094871,"text":"like the TV series \"Keeping Score\" with the San Francisco Symphony"},{"time":1098250,"text":"that looks at the backstories of music,"},{"time":1100817,"text":"and working with the young musicians at the New World Symphony"},{"time":1103994,"text":"on projects that explore the potential"},{"time":1105588,"text":"of the new performing arts centers"},{"time":1109094,"text":"for both entertainment and education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1111468,"text":"And of course, the New World Symphony"},{"time":1113435,"text":"led to the YouTube Symphony and projects on the internet"},{"time":1117083,"text":"that reach out to musicians and audiences all over the world."},{"time":1120087,"text":"And the exciting thing is all this is just a prototype."},{"time":1124867,"text":"There's just a role here for so many people --"},{"time":1127121,"text":"teachers, parents, performers --"},{"time":1129917,"text":"to be explorers together."},{"time":1132777,"text":"Sure, the big events attract a lot of attention,"},{"time":1135562,"text":"but what really matters is what goes on every single day."},{"time":1139042,"text":"We need your perspectives, your curiosity, your voices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143512,"text":"And it excites me now to meet people"},{"time":1146602,"text":"who are hikers, chefs, code writers, taxi drivers,"},{"time":1149700,"text":"people I never would have guessed who loved the music"},{"time":1152465,"text":"and who are passing it on."},{"time":1153580,"text":"You don't need to worry about knowing anything."},{"time":1157321,"text":"If you're curious, if you have a capacity for wonder, if you're alive,"},{"time":1161083,"text":"you know all that you need to know."},{"time":1164143,"text":"You can start anywhere. Ramble a bit."},{"time":1166352,"text":"Follow traces. Get lost. Be surprised, amused inspired."},{"time":1170456,"text":"All that 'what', all that 'how' is out there"},{"time":1175075,"text":"waiting for you to discover its 'why',"},{"time":1177569,"text":"to dive in and pass it on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180627,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1183125,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}